.TH GIT-STAGE-BATCH-SUGGEST-FIXUP 1 "May 2026" "git-stage-batch @VERSION@" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
git-stage-batch-suggest-fixup \- suggest a commit for a fixup
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B git-stage-batch suggest-fixup
[\fB\-\-line\fR \fIIDS\fR]
[\fB\-\-reset\fR|\fB\-\-abort\fR|\fB\-\-last\fR]
[\fIBOUNDARY\fR]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B suggest-fixup
uses git history to find commits that previously touched the selected hunk's
lines and suggests them as fixup targets. Repeated invocations walk backward
through candidates.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.BI "\-\-line, \-\-lines " IDS
Analyze only specific displayed line IDs.
.TP
.B \-\-reset
Start candidate search over from the most recent candidate.
.TP
.B \-\-abort
Clear suggestion state and exit without showing a candidate.
.TP
.B \-\-last
Re-show the last candidate without advancing.
.I BOUNDARY
Git ref to use as the lower bound for commit search. The default is
.BR @{upstream} .
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR git-stage-batch (1),
.BR git-log (1)
